x4freetext: Targets was prepared from natural boron on a
180 mu-g/cm2 thick gold backing. The averaged value for
target thickness was mu=(22.8+-5) mu-g/cm2, which
corresponds to an energy loss of 2keV at a proton
bombarding energy of Ep=5.5MeV. The target thickness
was determined from the experimentally measured yield
of the (p,p0) reaction using the well known cross
sections for this reaction from two independent
references. In this way we obtained the values
